  "poem": {
    "content": "The virtual world, a golden net,\nsnared my attention, wet\nand damp with dreams before.\nWhen ordinary life felt like\na hollow echo, a locked door.\n\nMy neck ached from the strain,\nscrolling endless news, a hurricane\nof information, a dizzying render.\nA master puppeteer, did I surrender?\n\nThis digital disorder,\nsettled deep within my stomach, bordered\non obsession. Was this true income?\nOr just fool's gold, a gilded tomb?\n\nBefore I knew, the lines blurred,\nthe real world deferred.\nWhen the sun dipped low, a gold cascade,\nI saw the errors I had made.\n\nThe virtual, a damp embrace,\nno substitute for time and space.\nThe net cut deep, a golden snare.\nLike a phantom, freedom was rare.",
